.TH "platform_pre_restore" 9 "platform_pre_restore" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
platform_pre_restore \- Prepare for hibernate image restoration.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" platform_pre_restore
.BI "(int platform_mode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "platform_mode" 12
Whether or not to use the platform driver.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Use the platform driver to prepare the system for resume from a hibernation
image.

If the restore fails after this function has been called,
\fBplatform_restore_cleanup\fP must be called.
